  "prompt": "Do you have a list of the questions that you were asked in the KVPY SA interview?",
  "response": "Sure, I can provide some common types of questions that are typically asked in the KVPY SA interview based on the experiences shared by previous candidates. The interview often includes questions across various subjects such as Physics, Chemistry, Mathematics, and Biology. Here are some examples:\n\n### Physics:\n1. Explain the working principle of a refrigerator.\n2. What is the Doppler Effect? How does it work?\n3. Describe Newton's laws of motion with examples.\n4. What are interference and diffraction in waves?\n\n### Chemistry:\n1. What is the periodic table? Can you explain its significance?\n2. Describe the process of electrolysis.\n3. Explain the types of chemical bonds.\n4. What is the difference between isotopes and isomers?\n\n### Mathematics:\n1. Can you solve this algebraic equation?\n2. Explain the concept of limits and continuity.\n3. What are the basic properties of triangles?\n4. Discuss the Pythagorean theorem.\n\n### Biology:\n1. Describe the structure of a DNA molecule.\n2. What are the basic steps involved in the process of photosynthesis?\n3. How do enzymes work in the human body?\n4. Explain the concept of genetic inheritance.\n\n### General Questions:\n1. Why did you choose to apply for the KVPY fellowship?\n2. What are your favorite subjects and why?\n3. Discuss any recent scientific research or discovery that has fascinated you.\n\nKeep in mind that if you're preparing for the KVPY SA interview, it is important to have a thorough understanding of the concepts from your textbooks and be able to apply them practically. It's recommended to go through NCERT books and other standard reference materials for deep insights. Good luck with your preparation!",
